com.gh.bmd.jrt.channel

Interface InputChannel<INPUT>

  • Type Parameters:
    INPUT - the input data type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Channel
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ParameterChannel<INPUT,OUTPUT>, ResultChannel<OUTPUT>, StandaloneChannel.StandaloneInput<INPUT>

    public interface InputChannel<INPUT>
extends Channel
    Interface defining an input channel.

    Note that the delivery order of the input data might not be guaranteed.

    Created by davide on 9/4/14.

    • Method Detail

      • after

        @Nonnull
InputChannel<INPUT> after(@Nonnull
                                TimeDuration delay)
        Tells the channel to delay the transfer of data of the specified time duration.
        Note that an abort command will be delayed as well. Note, however, that a delayed abort will not prevent the invocation from completing, as input data do.
        Parameters:
        delay - the delay.
        Returns:
        this channel.
        Throws:
        RoutineException - if the execution has been aborted.
        IllegalStateException - if this channel is already closed.
        NullPointerException - if the specified delay is null.

      • after

                                @Nonnull
                                TimeUnit timeUnit)
        Tells the channel to delay the transfer of data of the specified time duration.
        Note that an abort command will be delayed as well. Note, however, that a delayed abort will not prevent the invocation from completing, as input data do.
        Parameters:
        delay - the delay value.
        timeUnit - the delay time unit.
        Returns:
        this channel.
        Throws:
        RoutineException - if the execution has been aborted.
        IllegalArgumentException - if the specified delay is negative.
        IllegalStateException - if this channel is already closed.

      • pass

        @Nonnull
InputChannel<INPUT> pass(@Nullable
                               OutputChannel<? extends INPUT> channel)
        Passes the specified channel to this one.

        Note that this channel will be bound as a result of the call, thus preventing any other reader getting data from the specified output channel.

        Parameters:
        channel - the output channel.
        Returns:
        this channel.
        Throws:
        RoutineException - if the execution has been aborted.
        IllegalStateException - if this channel is already closed.
        See Also:
        OutputChannel.bind(OutputConsumer)
